        "breadcrumb_label": "About Valor",
        "hero_eyebrow": "About Valor Communication",
        "hero_title": "Ahead of the curve. <em><strong>Already on the shelf.</strong></em>",
        "hero_image": "shopify://shop_images/Valor_Warehouse.png",
        "hero_image_alt": "Valor distribution center building",
        "hero_image_placeholder": "",
        "story_num": "01 - Origin",
        "story_title": "Here before wireless was everywhere. Still ahead of <em><strong>what's next.</strong></em>",
        "story_label": "Founded",
        "story_year": "1997",
        "story_place": "Los Angeles, California",
        "story_image": "shopify://shop_images/Valor_phones_archive.png",
        "story_image_alt": "Early 2000s Era Wireless Phones",
        "story_image_placeholder": "",
        "story_body": "<p>Valor Communication started in Los Angeles in 1997 with a wholesale operation built for the people who actually move wireless accessories - independent dealers, regional distributors, master agents, and the buyers stocking shelves at retail. The work was practical from day one: get the right product built, priced, packed, shipped, and ready before demand turned into a missed sale.</p><p>That channel-first mindset shaped a company designed to last, scale, and keep pace with how wireless accessories actually sell. Tooling, packaging, freight, MOQs, terms, fulfillment, manufacturing, testing, and certifications were never background details - they were the operating system. <strong>Every part of the business was designed around what holds up at the point of sale</strong>, not what looks good in a corporate lookbook.</p><p>Nearly 30 years later, those wholesale roots have grown into a full-scale wireless accessory partner with the product depth, supply chain control, and channel reach to support demand across every major wireless path to sale.</p>",
        "story_quote": "We do not build brands and hope the channel catches up. We build brands made to move through it.",
        "story_body_after_quote": "<p>Today the operation spans <strong>250,000 square feet of fulfillment</strong> across California and Texas, a Shenzhen-based manufacturing arm running since 1999, and a portfolio of in-house brands covering protection, power, audio, attachables, and wearables. Product development, engineering, manufacturing, fulfillment, and custom programs now work as one connected system - from packaging through retail execution. Fewer handoffs, cleaner supply chains, more products ready where demand shows up.</p><p>Programs reach <strong>21,000+ retail locations at a 99% on-time delivery rate</strong> across major carrier networks, national retail, off-price chains, home improvement, OEM programs, and digital marketplaces. Retail intelligence, demand planning, inventory support, global logistics, and POS-ready integration help partners manage more than product availability - they help manage the systems that keep products stocked, moving, and selling.</p><p>What changed over those years is the depth of the operation. What didn't is the customer at the center of it: the operator selling phones at street level, the buyer stocking a planogram, the merchandiser picking next quarter's assortment, and the partner who needs the right products ready before the next ask hits.</p><p>The infrastructure scaled. The work didn't. <strong>Partners keep coming back because Valor keeps showing up.</strong></p>",
        "interstitial_image": "shopify://shop_images/valor_warehouse_team_motion.png",
        "interstitial_image_alt": "Valor warehouse team in motion",
        "interstitial_image_placeholder": "Warehouse, fulfillment floor, or product detail at scale",
        "values_num": "02 - Mission & Values",
        "values_title": "The way <em><strong>we operate.</strong></em>",
        "mission_label": "Mission",
        "mission_copy": "<p>Help retailers, carriers, and wireless partners <em>move faster</em> with accessory solutions built for real market demand - making the path from concept to shelf cleaner, quicker, and a lot less complicated.</p>",
        "channel_num": "03 - Channel Expertise",
        "channel_title": "We don't change the channel. We know <em><strong>how to work it.</strong></em>",
        "channel_image": "shopify://shop_images/Valor_AWPE_2025.jpg",
        "channel_image_alt": "Valor at AWPE Las Vegas",
        "channel_image_placeholder": "",
        "channel_lead": "<p>Every channel has its own pace, pressure points, and path to sale. <strong>Carrier programs don't move like off-price buys. Marketplace velocity doesn't move like a national retail reset. Dealer counters don't move like big-box planograms.</strong></p><p>Valor supports partners with channel-specific execution across assortment planning, packaging compliance, fulfillment, retail intelligence, API/EDI integration, and inventory visibility - keeping the right accessories ready for the channels that need them next.</p>",
        "channel_kicker": "<p>Because the accessory aisle isn't just an add-on. <em>Done right, it's a revenue engine hiding in plain sight.</em></p>",
        "closing_image": "shopify://shop_images/Valor_lifestyle_product.jpg",
        "closing_image_alt": "Valor product lifestyle scene",
        "closing_image_placeholder": "",
        "closing_eyebrow": "04 - Open accounts & partner programs",
        "closing_title": "You bring the business. <em><strong>We bring the backbone.</strong></em>",
        "closing_copy": "<p>If you operate a dealer location, master agent network, regional or national retail program, OEM program, off-price business, or marketplace operation - Valor is ready to help make your wireless accessory program stronger from the first shipment to the next reorder. <strong>You bring the business. We bring the infrastructure to keep it moving.</strong></p>",
        "primary_label": "Apply for an account",
        "primary_link": "",
        "secondary_label": "Contact us",
        "secondary_link": ""
      }
    },
